This same behavior is happening with euca2ools.  Another item that I noticed in my environment.  Now if I change the quota to allow '1' IP address, I am not allowed to allocate any IP addresses.  If I change the quota to '2', I can only allocate 1 IP address.  Here is the quota that gets created from the UI:
{code}
{
  "Version": "2011-04-01", 
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Action": "ec2:AllocateAddress", 
      "Resource": "*", 
      "Effect": "Limit", 
      "Condition": {
        "NumericLessThanEquals": {
          "ec2:quota-addressnumber": "1"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
{code}
I used this same configuration using euca2ools.
